  "response_text": "Creating a meal plan for weight loss involves focusing on nutrient-dense foods, maintaining a calorie deficit, and ensuring a balance of macronutrients (proteins, fats, and carbohydrates). Below is a sample 7-day meal plan designed to promote weight loss. This plan is balanced, easy to follow, and includes a variety of foods to keep meals interesting.\n\n### 7-Day Weight Loss Meal Plan\n\n#### Day 1\n- **Breakfast**: Greek yogurt (1 cup) with mixed berries (1/2 cup) and a sprinkle of chia seeds (1 tbsp).\n- **Snack**: A small apple with 1 tablespoon of almond butter.\n- **Lunch**: Grilled chicken salad with mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumber, and vinaigrette dressing.\n- **Snack**: Carrot sticks with hummus (2 tbsp).\n- **Dinner**: Baked salmon (4 oz) with steamed broccoli and quinoa (1/2 cup).\n\n#### Day 2\n- **Breakfast**: Oatmeal (1/2 cup dry) made with water; topped with sliced banana and a sprinkle of cinnamon.\n- **Snack**: A handful of almonds (about 1 oz).\n- **Lunch**: Turkey wrap with whole wheat tortilla, lettuce, tomato, and mustard; side of mixed fruit.\n- **Snack**: Celery sticks with 2 tablespoons of peanut butter.\n- **Dinner**: Stir-fried tofu (4 oz) with mixed vegetables (bell peppers, broccoli, and carrots) served over brown rice (1/2 cup).\n\n#### Day 3\n- **Breakfast**: Smoothie with spinach, banana, protein powder, and unsweetened almond milk.\n- **Snack**: Greek yogurt (1/2 cup) with a small handful of walnuts.\n- **Lunch**: Lentil soup (1 cup) with a side salad (mixed greens, cucumber, and olive oil).\n- **Snack**: Sliced bell peppers with guacamole (2 tbsp).\n- **Dinner**: Grilled shrimp (4 oz) with asparagus and a small sweet potato.\n\n#### Day 4\n- **Breakfast**: Scrambled eggs (2) with spinach and tomatoes, served with a slice of whole-grain toast.\n- **Snack**: A pear or a small orange.\n- **Lunch**: Quinoa salad with chickpeas, diced cucumber, cherry tomatoes, and a lemon-tahini dressing.\n- **Snack**: A small handful of mixed nuts.\n- **Dinner**: Baked chicken breast (4 oz) with roasted Brussels sprouts and brown rice (1/2 cup).\n\n#### Day 5\n- **Breakfast**: Chia pudding made with almond milk (1/4 cup chia seeds, 1 cup almond milk), topped with fresh fruit.\n- **Snack**: Cucumber slices with tzatziki sauce (2 tbsp).\n- **Lunch**: Spinach and feta stuffed bell peppers with a side of mixed greens.\n- **Snack**: A small peach or nectarine.\n- **Dinner**: Grilled turkey burger (no bun) with a side of roasted cauliflower.\n\n#### Day 6\n- **Breakfast**: Whole grain toast with avocado (1/2) and poached egg (1).\n- **Snack**: A small handful of trail mix (nuts and dried fruit).\n- **Lunch**: Chicken Caesar salad (light dressing, no croutons).\n- **Snack**: Cherry tomatoes with mozzarella balls (1 oz).\n- **Dinner**: Cod (4 oz) with sautéed kale and a small baked potato.\n\n#### Day 7\n- **Breakfast**: Smoothie bowl with blended frozen berries, topped with sliced banana and granola (1/4 cup).\n- **Snack**: Hard-boiled egg (1).\n- **Lunch**: Black bean salad with corn, diced tomatoes, red onion, and avocado.\n- **Snack**: Radishes and cucumber with balsamic vinegar.\n- **Dinner**: Grilled steak (4 oz) with a side of green beans and quinoa (1/2 cup).\n\n### Tips for Success\n- **Hydration**: Drink plenty of water throughout the day (aim for at least 8 cups).\n- **Portion Control**: Be mindful of portion sizes, especially with higher-calorie foods like nuts and oils.\n- **Meal Prep**: Prepare meals in advance to avoid unhealthy choices when you’re busy or tired.\n- **Physical Activity**: Incorporate regular exercise into your routine to enhance weight loss efforts.\n\n### Note\nThis meal plan is a general guideline. Individual calorie needs may vary based on age, gender, activity level, and specific health conditions. It’s advisable to consult with a healthcare professional or a registered dietitian before starting any weight loss plan.",
